He became just the ninth player in league history to average at least 20 points, 10 rebounds and five assists, posting career-highs in all three categories.

Starting all 82 games, Kevin put up career highs in scoring (23.0), rebounds (13.4), assists (6.0 ) and minutes (40.5).

Kevin topped Minnesota in rebounding all five games and averaged just under 30 points a night.

